Carlton George Douglas (born 10 May 1942) is a Jamaican singer-songwriter and recording artist who is best known for the 1974 disco single "Kung Fu Fighting".
His disco single "Kung Fu Fighting" ranked number one on both the U.K. Singles Chart and the U.S. Billboard Hot 100 in 1974.
The single was later certified Gold by the RIAA on 27 November 1974.
In 1998, a re-recording of "Kung Fu Fighting", performed by British dance act Bus Stop and which featured Douglas's vocals, peaked at number 8 in the UK Singles Chart.

The single "Dance the Kung Fu", was sampled on "Cuda nie widy" from the 2001 album Nibylandia by Polish group Ego, and later by DJ Premier on his 2007 remix of Nike's 25th Air Force One anniversary single "Classic (Better Than I've Ever Been)", featuring Kanye West, Nas, KRS-One, and Rakim.
